# Org

Layer-3 knowledge: organizational context that frames the user's working life. Always in context.

> **This is a template.** Copy it to your content vault as `kb/org.md` and replace the placeholder entries with real ones. The method repo never holds the real file.

Each entry follows the format:

```
## <Org / unit / team name>
- **Relation to user:** <one line>
- **Last verified:** <YYYY-MM-DD>
- **Expires:** <YYYY-MM-DD or never>
- **Source:** <file / URL / manual>

<short body — ≤120 words.>
```

Add teams, divisions, recurring vendor relationships, etc. The assistant never invents org details — populate from real sources.

---

## <Your Employer / Org Name>

- **Relation to user:** <e.g., employer, primary client, current contracting org>
- **Last verified:** <YYYY-MM-DD>
- **Expires:** <date or 'never (refresh on role/org change)'>
- **Source:** <pointer that grounds the entry — email domain, an org chart doc, etc.>

<short body about the org. Keep to facts the assistant should treat as ground
truth — internal team / product / role details that shape how to answer questions
about the user's working life. Don't invent — populate from real artifacts you
add to your harvest sources.>

## <A Specific Team / Project Within The Org>

- **Relation to user:** <e.g., "team I lead", "product I'm responsible for", "partnership with Vendor X">
- **Last verified:** <YYYY-MM-DD>
- **Expires:** <date or 'never'>
- **Source:** <pointer to a real document or thread>

<short body. The unit-level entries help the assistant disambiguate when
multiple programs or partnerships come up in harvested content.>
